HEADWORD: Cooper
<hw>Coop"er</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Coop</er>.]</ety> <def>One who makes barrels, hogsheads, casks,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cooper</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cooper
<hw>Coop"er</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Coopered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Coopering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To do the work of a cooper
upon; <as>as, to <ex>cooper</ex> a cask or barrel</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cooperage</ent>⟦br⟧
